Bashevis_Singer#cite_note-nobellecture-2\"><span>[<\/span>2<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> He also was awarded two U.S. <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/National_Book_Award\" title=\"National Book Award\">National Book Awards<\/a>, <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/National_Book_Award_for_Young_People%27s_Literature\" title=\"National Book Award for Young People's Literature\">one in Children's Literature<\/a> for his memoir <i>A Day Of Pleasure: Stories of a Boy Growing Up in Warsaw<\/i> (1970)<sup id=\"cite_ref-nba1970_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Isaac_Bashevis_Singer#cite_note-nba1970-3\"><span>[<\/span>3<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/National_Book_Award_for_Fiction\" title=\"National Book Award for Fiction\">one in Fiction<\/a> for his collection, <i><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/A_Crown_of_Feathers_and_Other_Stories\" title=\"A Crown of Feathers and Other Stories\">A Crown of Feathers and Other Stories<\/a><\/i> (1974).<sup id=\"cite_ref-nba1974_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Isaac_Bashevis_Singer#cite_note-nba1974-4\"><span>[<\/span>4<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p>","name":"Isaac Bashevis Singer","place_of_birth":"Leoncin, Poland","place_of_death":"Miami, Florida, USA","text":"Isaac Bashevis Singer ,  born in then Russian Empire, now Poland , Literature, 1978","year":1978.0}